[2] Outbreak summaries: CIDRAP (Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy)
- Mon 21 Sep 2020. News Scan
[CIDRAP (Center for Infectious Disease Research and Policy) abridged, edited]
https://www.cidrap.umn.edu/news-perspective/2020/09/news-scan-sep-21-2020

DRC Ebola outbreak total grows by 1 to reach 124 cases, with 50 deaths
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Tests confirmed 1 new Ebola infection in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) Equateur province outbreak, raising the total to 124, the United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (UN OCHA) said today [21 Sep 2020] in a situation update.

The latest case was reported from Lotumbe health zone. No new deaths were reported, keeping the total at 50.

The latest outbreak is concerning because of stretched resources due to the COVID-19 pandemic, a wide area where cases have been reported, and some sick patients remaining in the community, raising the risk of further virus spread.

--
